1
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:16,290
No one can really imagine...

2
00:00:16,660 --> 00:00:18,290
what it will be like after death.

3
00:00:18,570 --> 00:00:19,640
Until you...

4
00:00:20,580 --> 00:00:21,410
Wait. Wait...

5
00:00:21,410 --> 00:00:22,610
I didn't curse you.

6
00:00:23,380 --> 00:00:25,020
In most movies or books...

7
00:00:25,320 --> 00:00:27,280
it is often said that your body will lighter.

8
00:00:27,720 --> 00:00:29,640
And you will walk towards a white light.

9
00:00:30,010 --> 00:00:31,120
Seriously...

10
00:00:31,530 --> 00:00:33,520
I didn't see anyt white light at all.

11
00:00:34,290 --> 00:00:35,330
When I realized it...

12
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:36,970
Well, here I am, as you can see.

13
00:00:37,400 --> 00:00:38,680
I have no memories.

14
00:00:39,450 --> 00:00:41,610
Actually, I have been living here for more than 20 years.

15
00:00:42,320 --> 00:00:44,340
Who said that when you die time stops?

16
00:00:44,780 --> 00:00:45,680
That's not true.

17
00:00:46,480 --> 00:00:47,320
Here...

18
00:00:47,820 --> 00:00:49,500
you may close your eyes this year

19
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:51,500
and when you open them again...

20
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:53,500
It could be just a minute...

21
00:00:54,010 --> 00:00:55,810
or maybe a year that has passed.

22
00:00:56,810 --> 00:00:58,360
And the reason I care about counting time...

23
00:00:59,540 --> 00:01:01,090
is because of one person.

24
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:04,250
The one who makes me wait until next year.

25
00:01:05,520 --> 00:01:07,490
Waiting for the next Chingming to arrive.

26
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,000
But today...

27
00:01:11,210 --> 00:01:13,290
I finally came back here again.

28
00:01:15,290 --> 00:01:17,200
When the truth was revealed,

29
00:01:17,940 --> 00:01:19,500
The truth that happened...

30
00:01:20,100 --> 00:01:22,420
on my 22nd birthday...

31
00:01:23,370 --> 00:01:25,090
and the same day I died.

32
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:26,690
1997
Mes's Birthday

33
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:34,980
Pad Kra Pao is Holy Basil Stir-fry dish

34
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:34,980
Looks like you are getting fed up with Pad Kra Pao.

35
00:04:38,330 --> 00:04:39,120
No khrap.

36
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:41,440
I'm just not hungry.

37
00:04:45,010 --> 00:04:48,120
If you just didn't feel hungry,
 you wouldn't have such a long face.

38
00:04:48,690 --> 00:04:49,690
Is there anyhing bothering you?

39
00:04:53,620 --> 00:04:54,010
Hmm?

40
00:04:55,620 --> 00:04:57,650
I miss Dad and Mom, Auntie Nom.

41
00:05:03,620 --> 00:05:05,580
They are resting in peace.

42
00:05:09,420 --> 00:05:12,410
How about I prepare food tomorrow as an 
offering to the monks for a blessing for them?

43
00:05:15,060 --> 00:05:15,770
That is great khrap.

44
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:17,500
Thank you, Auntie.

45
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:20,610
Then...

46
00:05:20,850 --> 00:05:22,360
smile, please?

47
00:05:22,640 --> 00:05:25,010
So your parents can see and easy...

48
00:05:25,010 --> 00:05:26,320
that you are living happily,

49
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:28,320
Okay?

50
00:05:29,890 --> 00:05:30,320
Khrap.

51
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:33,100
Oh,

52
00:05:33,440 --> 00:05:34,770
since it is your birthday kha,

53
00:05:34,770 --> 00:05:36,180
will you go celebrate with your friends?

54
00:05:38,250 --> 00:05:39,960
I am not planning on going anywhere, Auntie.

55
00:05:40,410 --> 00:05:41,960
By 10 PM, I would be sleepy.

56
00:05:42,540 --> 00:05:43,620
It wouldn't be fun to go out.

57
00:05:45,620 --> 00:05:46,660
It's up to you then kha.

58
00:05:51,060 --> 00:05:51,520
Oh?

59
00:05:51,810 --> 00:05:52,820
Are you full already kha?

60
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:55,700
Then take your medicine kha.

61
00:06:11,220 --> 00:06:11,850
Here, water.

62
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:12,460
Thank you khrap.

63
00:06:12,460 --> 00:06:13,560
Take the medicine kha.

64
00:07:49,740 --> 00:07:50,610
I remember it now.

65
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,520
Before I died,

66
00:07:54,850 --> 00:07:56,460
I saw someone at the door.

67
00:07:57,020 --> 00:07:57,810
Who was it, P'?

68
00:08:10,730 --> 00:08:11,600
Uncle Phop?

69
00:08:12,420 --> 00:08:13,140
Auntie Nom?

70
00:08:18,020 --> 00:08:18,900
Grandpa.

71
00:08:21,980 --> 00:08:23,330
Is Grandpa your uncle?

72
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:28,930
That means that your father is Grandpa's brother.

73
00:08:29,890 --> 00:08:31,320
What are you doing in here?

74
00:08:32,450 --> 00:08:33,780
Get out of here!

75
00:08:34,210 --> 00:08:35,500
My apologies khrap...

76
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:37,330
for not asking permission from you first.

77
00:08:37,330 --> 00:08:39,080
But I have some questions for you Grandpa khrap?

78
00:08:40,820 --> 00:08:42,340
Do you know someone named Mes khrap?

79
00:08:44,860 --> 00:08:45,800
Who is Mes?

80
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:47,960
I don't know.

81
00:08:48,370 --> 00:08:51,720
Mes, Wongsakorn Thanarungsiri.

82
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:54,440
There is no one with that name in this house.

83
00:09:04,810 --> 00:09:06,400
Then can can you tell me khrap...

84
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:08,970
who this person is in this photo?

85
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:13,460
Where did you gt his picture from?

86
00:09:13,460 --> 00:09:14,850
That isn't important khrap.

87
00:09:15,130 --> 00:09:16,850
are you going to admit now khrap...

88
00:09:16,850 --> 00:09:18,480
that you know P'Mes?

89
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:20,980
And that P'Mes is your nephew...

90
00:09:21,380 --> 00:09:22,650
who used to live here.

91
00:09:27,540 --> 00:09:28,260
 Yes.

92
00:09:29,820 --> 00:09:32,800
Mes is the son of my older brother.

93
00:09:33,890 --> 00:09:36,940
But he has been dead for more than 20 years already.

94
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:39,760
Why would you ask about him?

95
00:09:39,760 --> 00:09:41,240
Then can you tell me something khrap?

96
00:09:42,330 --> 00:09:45,100
Why everyone here let P'Mes 
become a ghost without relatives?

97
00:09:45,660 --> 00:09:47,100
Abandoned him at the cemetery

98
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:48,490
 and no one even visited.

99
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:50,090
And this room?

100
00:09:50,410 --> 00:09:52,090
Why did you lock up the room where P'Mes died?

101
00:09:53,460 --> 00:09:55,280
That is none of your business.

102
00:09:55,820 --> 00:09:57,020
The reason I came here...

103
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,020
is because I want to know

104
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:02,020
why P'Mes has been left like he doesn't exist.

105
00:10:02,540 --> 00:10:05,640
Why does everyone here act like P'Mes never existed?

106
00:10:07,100 --> 00:10:08,400
Why is that?

107
00:10:09,660 --> 00:10:14,100
Because I'm the one who ordered 
everyone not to talk about him again.

108
00:10:15,640 --> 00:10:17,080
Including this room.

109
00:10:19,610 --> 00:10:21,220
Mes was an unfortunate child.

110
00:10:23,220 --> 00:10:25,260
He had heart disease since he was born.

111
00:10:27,260 --> 00:10:29,850
Before his father and mother died...

112
00:10:31,060 --> 00:10:33,280
I promised his father...

113
00:10:34,930 --> 00:10:36,160
that I would take good care of him.

114
00:10:39,260 --> 00:10:40,880
But I didn't keep my word.

115
00:10:44,770 --> 00:10:46,480
After I lost my brother...

116
00:10:48,260 --> 00:10:49,970
and then to lose my nephew.

117
00:10:52,160 --> 00:10:53,840
 Do think that was easy?

118
00:10:54,560 --> 00:10:57,500
To see your family dying one after the other?

119
00:11:02,570 --> 00:11:03,730
On the day Mes died...

120
00:11:06,410 --> 00:11:08,960
was the worst day for the family.

121
00:11:12,540 --> 00:11:13,540
In this room...

122
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:17,080
This very spot...

123
00:11:18,740 --> 00:11:20,620
The more I see it, the more I remember it.

124
00:11:22,170 --> 00:11:24,140
Every single day, each day...

125
00:11:25,680 --> 00:11:26,770
If you were me...

126
00:11:27,930 --> 00:11:29,940
do you think you could overcome this feeling?

127
00:11:37,240 --> 00:11:41,760
So you left P'Mes at the cemetery?

128
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:43,810
It is my fault.

129
00:11:46,300 --> 00:11:47,800
It is my fault I have never visited him there.

130
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:51,330
I have never prayed for him.

131
00:11:53,850 --> 00:11:55,980
Every time I see something about Mes,

132
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:00,780
it makes me feel even more regret.

133
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:06,040
I regret that I didn't take care of him well enough.

134
00:12:09,300 --> 00:12:10,900
<i>I don't want to talk about this anymore.</i>

135
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,600
 That's enough, Thun.

136
00:12:24,220 --> 00:12:25,930
I feel sorry for you, Grandpa.

137
00:12:26,690 --> 00:12:29,020
<i>That you have had to suffer for this.</i>

138
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:31,020
<i>I understand...</i>

139
00:12:32,010 --> 00:12:33,540
<i>that you want to forget about him.</i>

140
00:12:35,540 --> 00:12:37,940
But isn't it because you feel guilty...

141
00:12:38,540 --> 00:12:41,680
<i>that you let P'Mes die without helping him?</i>

142
00:12:42,290 --> 00:12:43,200
Thun!

143
00:12:43,970 --> 00:12:45,850
What are you trying to say?

144
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:49,860
Stop talking nonsense.

145
00:12:50,050 --> 00:12:51,600
I am not talking nonsense.

146
00:12:52,540 --> 00:12:55,690
P'Mes told me that Grandpa you 
stood by and watched him die!

147
00:12:57,760 --> 00:12:58,600
Ai'Thun.

148
00:13:00,850 --> 00:13:02,680
What kind of child are you?

149
00:13:03,970 --> 00:13:05,960
Why are you slandering someone older than you like this?

150
00:13:06,770 --> 00:13:07,440
Thun...

151
00:13:07,940 --> 00:13:09,300
that's enough!

152
00:13:09,740 --> 00:13:12,180
You have made him sad enough.

153
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:14,360
I have to say this khrap.

154
00:13:16,130 --> 00:13:18,020
Everything that happened...

155
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:21,220
is my family matter.

156
00:13:23,220 --> 00:13:24,290
It's none of your business.

157
00:13:24,930 --> 00:13:25,690
It is my business.

158
00:13:26,250 --> 00:13:27,410
The reason I'm saying this...

159
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:30,650
 is because I'm the only one who can communicate with P'Mes.

160
00:13:34,530 --> 00:13:35,500
I don't believe you.

161
00:13:37,820 --> 00:13:40,340
Stop lying to your elder.

162
00:13:41,420 --> 00:13:42,940
Get out of my house.

163
00:13:43,880 --> 00:13:46,120
Or I'll call the police to arrest you...

164
00:13:46,810 --> 00:13:48,730
for breaking and entering.

165
00:13:49,210 --> 00:13:50,800
I'm not going anywhere.

166
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:54,290
Until I know the truth.

167
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:57,250
In order for me to help P'Mes...

168
00:13:57,480 --> 00:13:59,760
I need to know why P'Mes can't be reincarnated!

169
00:13:59,760 --> 00:14:01,500
Mes died a long time ago!

170
00:14:02,210 --> 00:14:02,970
Khun...

171
00:14:03,090 --> 00:14:04,640
It has nothing to do with you!

172
00:14:05,060 --> 00:14:05,780
Calm down, please.

173
00:14:05,780 --> 00:14:06,580
Get out!

174
00:14:07,090 --> 00:14:08,490
Get out of here!

175
00:14:08,490 --> 00:14:09,170
Khun...

176
00:14:09,170 --> 00:14:10,860
Even if you kick me out of this house...

177
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:13,820
you can't get rid of  P'Mes his house khrap!

178
00:14:23,060 --> 00:14:24,500
Do you believe me now...

179
00:14:24,740 --> 00:14:26,290
that P'Mes is here!?!

180
00:14:33,180 --> 00:14:33,900
Mes?

181
00:14:39,560 --> 00:14:40,500
Uncle Phop!

182
00:14:42,060 --> 00:14:44,460
Why didn't you help me that day?

183
00:14:45,370 --> 00:14:47,410
Why didn't you do anything?

184
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:49,410
Now can you answer my question khrap?

185
00:14:50,760 --> 00:14:53,040
Why didn't you help P'Mes that day?

186
00:14:59,850 --> 00:15:00,640
Khun...

187
00:15:02,300 --> 00:15:03,080
Khun...

188
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:04,210
I was wrong.

189
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:09,370
I didn't mean for it to happen that way.

190
00:15:15,060 --> 00:15:17,540
<i>I still remember that it was Mes' birthday.</i>

191
00:15:21,680 --> 00:15:23,680
Here it is.

192
00:15:23,930 --> 00:15:25,680
The chocolate cake...

193
00:15:25,940 --> 00:15:28,440
I was the one who asked Nom to buy it.

194
00:15:29,940 --> 00:15:32,720
Everyone in the house was preparing his birthday surprise.

195
00:15:34,720 --> 00:15:36,360
I went to go get him.

196
00:15:37,740 --> 00:15:38,960
But when I got there,

197
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:41,760
Mes was already on the floor.

198
00:15:43,290 --> 00:15:44,340
I was shocked.

199
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:46,010
I couldn't move.

200
00:15:46,760 --> 00:15:49,300
All of my strength left my body.

201
00:15:49,820 --> 00:15:51,090
I didn't know what to do.

202
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:53,690
I don't know what I should do.

203
00:15:54,450 --> 00:15:55,760
It was my fault.

204
00:15:56,210 --> 00:15:58,410
If I had helped Mes in time,

205
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:00,800
it wouldn't be like this.

206
00:16:01,480 --> 00:16:02,460
I regret this.

207
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:05,560
I feel terrible for letting him die.

208
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:07,080
It was my fault.

209
00:16:07,740 --> 00:16:08,690
I'm so sorry.

210
00:16:11,980 --> 00:16:13,360
I love you, Mes.

211
00:16:15,730 --> 00:16:17,170
<i>When you were alive...</i>

212
00:16:18,460 --> 00:16:20,200
<i>I did my best to take care of you.</i>

213
00:16:21,620 --> 00:16:22,820
I took you to the hospital...

214
00:16:23,140 --> 00:16:24,820
and made sure you always had your medicine.

215
00:16:25,700 --> 00:16:27,160
You can ask Nom about this.

216
00:16:29,320 --> 00:16:31,880
<i>I tried to do everything I could.</i>

217
00:16:33,740 --> 00:16:35,620
And if Mes hadn't of lost his medicine...

218
00:16:37,620 --> 00:16:38,860
you wouldn't have died.

219
00:16:42,640 --> 00:16:44,970
For 20 years, I have tried to forget this.

220
00:16:47,850 --> 00:16:49,930
and now you make me recount it.

221
00:16:52,090 --> 00:16:53,460
Why did you do this?

222
00:16:58,080 --> 00:16:59,820
We're sorry, Grandpa.

223
00:17:00,450 --> 00:17:02,060
You should apologize to Grandpa now.

224
00:17:02,130 --> 00:17:03,890
Grandpa is already feeling guilty about this.

225
00:17:04,540 --> 00:17:06,040
How could Grandpa know...

226
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:08,040
P'Mes would lose his medicine that day?

227
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:11,080
It might have really been P'Mes' time to die.

228
00:17:13,080 --> 00:17:14,050
P'Mes khrap,

229
00:17:14,330 --> 00:17:16,050
Please forgive Grandpa khrap.

230
00:17:20,130 --> 00:17:21,500
I saw your spirit...

231
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:22,530
 as red.

232
00:17:22,530 --> 00:17:24,020
What does that mean?

233
00:17:24,450 --> 00:17:26,020
You didn't die from a heart attack khrap.

234
00:17:29,140 --> 00:17:29,970
That's right khrap.

235
00:17:32,840 --> 00:17:35,260
You took care of P'Mes the best as you could, right?

236
00:17:36,980 --> 00:17:39,180
And you also asked Auntie Nom to care for him, right?

237
00:17:40,180 --> 00:17:41,180
Auntie Nom khrap...

238
00:17:42,690 --> 00:17:44,410
What do you remember about that day?

239
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:49,080
I am the one who took care of Khun Mes.

240
00:17:50,160 --> 00:17:52,980
Everyday, I prepared Khun Mes' food and his medicine myself.

241
00:17:53,490 --> 00:17:54,500
The boss always reminded me...

242
00:17:54,700 --> 00:17:56,180
that I shouldn't ever miss it.

243
00:17:56,180 --> 00:17:57,440
No matter what kind of medicine Khun Mes had...

244
00:17:58,940 --> 00:18:00,760
or if there was new medicine,

245
00:18:00,970 --> 00:18:02,020
or what dose...

246
00:18:02,020 --> 00:18:03,600
I was the one that knew.

247
00:18:04,930 --> 00:18:06,640
Was there anything out of the ordinary that day?

248
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:08,940
There wasn't.

249
00:18:09,580 --> 00:18:12,170
I still remember that the doctor had
 changed the medicine for him.

250
00:18:12,380 --> 00:18:13,340
New medicine?

251
00:18:13,520 --> 00:18:14,290
Wait khrap.

252
00:18:15,120 --> 00:18:17,000
How did you know it was a new medicine?

253
00:18:17,540 --> 00:18:17,960
Because...

254
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:21,410
I prepared his medicine myself everyday so I have to remember.

255
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:23,410
<i>How did you know...</i>

256
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:25,410
<i>which medicine was for what?</i>

257
00:18:26,820 --> 00:18:28,330
I didn't.

258
00:18:29,020 --> 00:18:30,330
Khun Mes had a lot of medicine.

259
00:18:30,530 --> 00:18:32,330
He also had a lot of vitamins.

260
00:18:32,330 --> 00:18:34,220
Master is the one who told me.

261
00:18:36,220 --> 00:18:37,370
Is it possible...

262
00:18:38,040 --> 00:18:39,370
that the new medicine...

263
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:41,000
was not to treat the heart...

264
00:18:41,260 --> 00:18:43,400
but to precipitate P'Mes's heart attack?

265
00:18:45,780 --> 00:18:47,300
Don't say such trash!

266
00:18:48,050 --> 00:18:49,520
Who would be crazy enough to do that?

267
00:18:49,520 --> 00:18:50,540
<i>That's true.</i>

268
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:52,100
Who would have done it?

269
00:18:52,760 --> 00:18:53,930
Let's think about it?

270
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:57,960
Who would inherit and benefit from P'Mes's property...

271
00:18:57,980 --> 00:18:59,820
if P'Mes were to die?

272
00:19:03,460 --> 00:19:07,540
You are accusing me of that I intentionally caused Mes to die, right?

273
00:19:07,900 --> 00:19:09,540
Wasn't that the case?

274
00:19:11,840 --> 00:19:14,000
If it wasn't, how do you explain...

